. Even though the simulated and observed filaments are subjectively\nsimilar-looking, we find that they behave in very different ways. The simulated\nfilaments are turbulence-dominated regions, the observed filaments are instead\nself-gravitating structures that will probably fragment into cores.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Sep 2015 13:16:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-16"}
